a Cicognini, ''[http://www.cineblog.it/post/43543/youmovie-awards-2012-ecco-i-vincitori-trionfa-la-talpa Cineblog.it]'' (30 June 2012)</ref>\n| rowspan=\"14\" | 30 June 2012\n| Best Film\n|\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Drama Film\n|\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Thriller\n|\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Actor in a Leading Role\n| Gary Oldman\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Supporting Actor\n| Benedict Cumberbatch\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Supporting Actor\n| Colin Firth\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Cast\n|\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Villain\n| Colin Firth\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Director\n| Tomas Alfredson\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Trailer\n|\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Cinematography\n| Hoyte Van Hoytema\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Art Direction\n| Maria Djurkovic\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Screenplay\n| Bridget O'Connor, Peter Straughan\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Costume Design\n| Jaqueline Durran\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[World Soundtrack Academy]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[World Soundtrack Awards 2012|20 October 2012]]\n| [[World Soundtrack Award for Best Original Score of the Year|Best Score of the Year]]\n| Alberto Iglesias\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[World Soundtrack Award for Soundtrack Composer of the Year|Best Composer of the Year]]\n| Alberto Iglesias\n| {{won}}\n|}\n\n==Possible sequel==\nWhile doing press for Working Title's ''[[Les Mis\u00e9rables (2012 film)|Les Mis\u00e9rables]]'' film adaptation, producer Eric Fellner stated that fellow producer Tim Bevan was working with writer Straughan and director Alfredson on developing a sequel to ''Tinker Tailor Soldier Spy''. Fellner did not specify whether or not the sequel would be based on ''[[The Honourable Schoolboy]]'' or ''[[Smiley's People]]'', the two remaining Smiley novels in Le Carr\u00e9's Karla trilogy.<ref>{{cite web|last=Chitwood|first=Adam|url=\nhttp://collider.com/tinker-tailor-soldier-spy-2-sequel-eric-fellner/217164/|title=Producer Eric Fellner Talks; Says Tomas Alfredson and Screenwriter Peter Straughan are Working on it \"As We Speak\"|work=Collider|date=11 December 2012|accessdate=11 December 2012}}</ref> While doing press for ''[[Dawn of the Planet of the Apes]]'' in 2014, Oldman stated that talk of a sequel, an adaptation of ''Smiley's People'', had since disappeared; while also stressing that he would still like to see the film produced.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://collider.com/keri-russell-gary-oldman-dawn-of-the-planet-of-the-apes-interview/|title=Keri Russell and Gary Oldman Talk DAWN OF THE PLANET OF THE APES|date=26 April 2014|work=Collider}}</ref> However, in July 2016 Oldman confirmed that the sequel was in its early stages, stating, \"There is a script, but I don't know when we will shoot.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/gossip/confidential/gary-oldman-return-tinker-tailor-soldier-spy-sequel-article-1.2701578|title=Gary Oldman to return in 'Tinker Tailor Soldier Spy' sequel|date=6 July 2016|work=NY Daily News}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n{{wikiquote}}\n* {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110923181843/http://www.tinker-tailor-soldier-spy.com/ |date=23 September 2011 |title=Official movie website }}\n* {{allrovi movie|541467}}\n* {{IMDb title|1340800}}\n\n{{John le Carr\u00e9}}\n{{Navboxes\n|title= Awards for ''Tinker Tailor Soldier Spy''\n|list1=\n{{BAFTA Best British Film}}\n{{Empire Award for Best British Film}}\n{{Empire Award for Best Thriller}}\n}}\n{{Tomas Alfredson}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2012}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tinker Tailor Soldier Spy}}\n[[Category:2011 films]]\n[[Category:2010s spy thriller films]]\n[[Category:British spy thriller films]]\n[[Category:British films]]\n[[Category:French spy thriller films]]\n[[Category:French films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Best British Film Empire Award winners]]\n[[Category:Best Thriller Empire Award winners]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Tomas Alfredson]]\n[[Category:Films based on works by John le Carr\u00e9]]\n[[Category:Cold Wa